@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Squarado" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile, the bar displayed on it will rotate
clockwise by 45 degres. To complicate matters a little, You cannot click
two or more times in a row on the same bar, as it will rotate only once;
you have to click on another bar before clicking again on the same bar.

  To create an alignment, 3 bars or more have to be lined-up and the
orientation of the bars must be the same as their alignment. In other
words: for an horizontal alignment, the bars must be horizontal.

  When an alignment of bars has been made, those bars will be removed
from the board and you will get points according to the number of bars
that were lined-up; 1 point for 3 bars, 10 points for 4 bars and 100
points for 5 bars.

  Continue the game until the board is emptied, in which case, Squarado
will display a new board. If no alignments of at least 3 bars can be
made, the game will be over.

  Squarado keeps the best score made since the game was run.

  Have fun!

@endnode

